metadata.name: Syzers #370
metadata.description:
Syzers is a generative synthesizer project with sounds altered by Tone JS.

···· On Tuesday, May 17, unsold editions will be burned ····

Visually it consists of 16 layers, in which more than 350 elements are combined randomly, generating synthesizers with unique environments and landscapes.
As for the sound, 40 tracks were recorded with analog synthesizers that were then assigned to each of the modules. These, combined in groups of 4, provide thousands of possible combinations. 
In addition, these sounds will be further modified by code effects that will randomly vary their properties.

Click to listen to the sounds

Many thanks to @Jpupper and @Fipiaggio for help with programming the sound part and @Purespider for the template. 
"FXHASH PFP Token Generator" https://github.com/PureSpider/fxhash-pfp

for best resolution "open live" then use the "download image" button on the lower right corner ;)

metadata.name: Los Osos 2422 #1804
metadata.description:
# Los Osos 2422

I was working on the next EmProps release when accidentally I opened a link to a bear utopic civilization through their existing metaverse. Or should I say "metabears"?

Enter Los Osos 2422. 

Four hundred years into the future bears live in a peaceful civilization heavily inspired by the generative art movement of our times. They are organized in districts that are sustained by bamboo, salmon, berries, and art! Los Osos are black, grizzly, panda, and polar, yet there are no distinctions between species; it's not like they were humans. 

They have different occupations but frequently bears change jobs giving birth to the most eclectic looks.

I took my sketchbook out to capture what I could and started drawing but my presence pissed them off. Ninjas, luchadores, and even a cybearpunk forced me to escape.  Is that a live gummy bear or am I just hungry? The story will continue...

-- 

Los Osos 2422 is a PFP art piece composed of 320 hand-made drawings made as an homage to the nascent generative art current fueled by Tezos blockchain technology in 2022. It features hundreds of references to artists and pieces in several generative and non-generative fields.

The project combines the assets together using a custom open-source algorithm that allows them to stack with the positioning in front and behind the character to create possibilities like shirt collars or hats, dynamic tinting to have hoodies or glasses with different colors, exceptions to give them laser eyes or a green apple in front of the face, complex set-ups to have different versions for some of the outfits, and chance control to allow precise control over the features.

--

Press 'S' on the keyboard to save it as an 1800 x 1800 pixels PNG.

*Nakachoii*
The Nakachoii soldiers from anime lands entered fxhash, this time to get new faces and new powers with the coding that is applied to them. metadata.name: carpet gate #34
metadata.description:
This artwork draws with broken lines creating a comfortable carpet pattern. I lived part of my life in a post-Soviet country where carpets hung in the apartment. Every night before going to bed I lay looking at his patterns.

Now I have created my carpets and I really hope that you will appreciate it. Carpets have always evoked only warm emotions of comfort, family and warmth.

metadata.name: CSS Crystals✨ #28
metadata.description:
This 3D HTML + CSS based work utilizes only a limited amount of javascript to construct the scene and facilitate interactive controls. 🚫 <canvas>! Continuing the collab with my alternate identity HTMLCSS.TEZ

The practice of layering many graphic shapes and gradients with a chaotic mix of blending modes has been with me since my first years of photoshop in my youth. It's a familiar, friendly technique. Yet, I've rarely played with it outside photoshop. Here I take the opportunity to apply this abstract blending technique in a manner that alludes to reality: refracting crystals.

These generated crystals are not based in fact but imagination. They are illustrative of the magic and wonder some people associate with real life minerals and rocks. They blend together with impossible color changes only possible in the virtual.

Each individual crystal element can be one of these blend modes (with chance):
difference (9/16), exclusion (2/16), hard-light (2/16), color-dodge (1/16), overlay (1/16), normal (1/16)

Controls:
Play/Pause - [Space]
Rotate - [Click + Drag]
Move - [Shit + Click + Drag]

Minter's Reward: 1/3 Secondary royalties

metadata.name: INTERFERENCES #127
metadata.description:
INTERFERENCES is an abstract representation of the incredible collaboration between artists, collectors and developers on fxhash.

Each edition is composed of a multitude of lines representing each individual on the platform. The color of each line defines the role of each individual in this universe. Through their interactions, and the interferences they produce, each line participates in the creation of a common work.

Happy birthday fxhash! And congratulations to all those who work for its success.

Primary sales are donated to the Processing Foundation

[TOUCHSCREEN]
* Double Tap to save the current image

[KEYBOARD]
* Press [S] to save the current image
* Press [1] to save a 1500x2000 pixels PNG
* Press [2] to save a 3000x4000 pixels PNG
* Press [3] to save a 6000x8000 pixels PNG
* Press [0] to save 3 individual SVG for each color set of lines + the background image PNG
* Press [9] to save a grouped SVG of all the lines + the background image PNG

Artist: Estienne
Nov. 2022
NFT License 2.0

Credits to Piter Pasma (@piterpasma) for the Reumann-Witkam line simplification algorithm used in this generator
